<br>
Hehe<br>
<br>
Ever been on a raid to the queen?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am not trying to discourage anyone that would like to do this.  I just don't know how doable this kind of raid is for a pick up group.<br>
<br>
Some things in Chardok make it different then most raids you will go on in your EQ life.<br>
<br>
1.  Repop<br>
Its pretty fast down there.  If your sitting around even for 5 min you chance repop and wipeout.  The raid has to keep killing/moving.  This means no AFKs and leaving your LDs to die and drag them back latter.  This kind of time constraint can get to people.  It can be stressfull.<br>
<br>
2. Runners<br>
I have seen entire raids wiped down in royals because 1 runner got away.  That takes some serious disipline to make sure thats done, because one getting way is raid ending.<br>
<br>
3. Cost<br>
Chardok raids are actally pretty darn exspensive unless its a complete sucess.  Typicaly untill you learn the zone really well it will end in a coffin CR.<br>
<br>
4. Traps<br>
There are traps in the royal area.  Even if you know where they are people will fall in them.  /shrug it always happens.<br>
<br>
<br>
I wish anyone luck who trys to put this together and this could be a great learning tool.  I bet with 2 or 3 runs you would get it down and start droping epic mobs.  I bet you even take a prince or 2 on your first few raids.<br>
<br>
